# SentinelIQ Unified Command Centre

## Overview
AI-powered web application built with Spring Boot, React, and Flask.

## Tech Stack
- Java 17 + Spring Boot 3.x
- PostgreSQL 15
- Redis 7
- Flyway migrations
- Spring Security + JWT
- Docker + Docker Compose

## Prerequisites
- Java 17
- Docker Desktop
- Node.js 18+
- Python 3.11

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/darshanhp9686/sentineliq-unified-command-centre.git
cd sentineliq-unified-command-centre

### 2. Create .env file
cp .env.example .env
Fill in your values in .env file

### 3. Run with Docker
docker-compose up --build

### 4. Access the app
- Frontend: http://localhost
- Backend API: http://localhost:8080
- Swagger UI: http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
- AI Service: http://localhost:5000

## Architecture
Frontend (React) → Backend (Spring Boot) → AI Service (Flask)
Backend connects to PostgreSQL and Redis

## Known Issues (P3 - Minor)
- Long titles truncate on mobile screens
- CSV export does not include audit log history
- Email notifications require valid SMTP configuration

## Team
- Java Developer 2: Database, REST API, Auth, Docker